#: src/1695-add-error-macro.md:9
msgid ""
"This RFC proposes adding a new macro to `libcore`, `compile_error!` which "
"will unconditionally cause compilation to fail with the given error message "
"when encountered."
msgstr ""

#: src/1695-add-error-macro.md:13
msgid "Motivation"
msgstr "動機"

#: src/1695-add-error-macro.md:16
msgid ""
"Crates which work with macros or annotations such as `cfg` have no tools to "
"communicate error cases in a meaningful way on stable. For example, given "
"the following macro:"
msgstr ""

#: src/1695-add-error-macro.md:27
msgid ""
"when invoked with `baz`, the error message will be `error: no rules expected "
"the token baz`. In a real world scenario, this error may actually occur deep "
"in a stack of macro calls, with an even more confusing error message. With "
"this RFC, the macro author could provide the following:"
msgstr ""

#: src/1695-add-error-macro.md:37
msgid "\"This macro only accepts `foo` or `bar`\""
msgstr ""

#: src/1695-add-error-macro.md:42
msgid ""
"When combined with attributes, this also provides a way for authors to "
"validate combinations of features."
msgstr ""

#: src/1695-add-error-macro.md:46
msgid "\"postgresql\""
msgstr ""

#: src/1695-add-error-macro.md:46
